Common Cybersecurity Threats

1. Insider Threat
Description
An insider threat occurs when a current or former employee, student, contractor, or authorized user intentionally or unintentionally causes harm to an organization's systems or data.
Possible Impact
•	Data theft or leakage
•	Unauthorized access to confidential information
•	Financial and reputational damage
•	Disruption of business operations
Prevention Methods
•	Implement access controls and least-privilege policies
•	Monitor user activities and system logs
•	Conduct employee security awareness training
•	Revoke access immediately when users leave the organization

2. Malware
Description
Malware is malicious software designed to damage, disrupt, or gain unauthorized access to computer systems and data.
Possible Impact
•	Data loss or corruption
•	System slowdown or crashes
•	Unauthorized access to sensitive information
•	Financial losses
Prevention Methods
•	Install and update antivirus software
•	Download software only from trusted sources
•	Keep operating systems updated
•	Avoid opening suspicious attachments and links

3. Phishing
Description
Phishing is a cyberattack in which attackers impersonate trusted organizations to trick users into revealing passwords, banking details, or other sensitive information.
Possible Impact
•	Account compromise
•	Identity theft
•	Financial fraud
•	Unauthorized access to systems
Prevention Methods
•	Verify email senders before responding
•	Avoid clicking suspicious links
•	Enable Multi-Factor Authentication (MFA)
•	Provide cybersecurity awareness training

4. Weak Passwords
Description
Weak passwords are easy-to-guess passwords that lack sufficient complexity and can be cracked by attackers.
Possible Impact
•	Unauthorized account access
•	Data breaches
•	Identity theft
•	Compromised organizational systems
Prevention Methods
•	Use long and complex passwords
•	Use unique passwords for each account
•	Enable Multi-Factor Authentication (MFA)
•	Use a password manager

5. Unpatched Systems
Description
Unpatched systems are computers or applications that have not received the latest security updates and fixes.
Possible Impact
•	Exploitation of known vulnerabilities
•	Malware infections
•	Data breaches
•	System compromise
Prevention Methods
•	Regularly install security updates and patches
•	Enable automatic updates where possible
•	Conduct vulnerability assessments
•	Maintain an effective patch management process
